In mathematics, the '''Church–Kleene ordinal''', <math>\omega^{\mathrm{CK}}_1</math>, named after [[Alonzo Church]] and [[S. C. Kleene]], is a [[large countable ordinal]]. It is the set of all [[recursive ordinal]]s and the smallest non-recursive ordinal. It is also the first ordinal which is not [[Hyperarithmetical theory|hyperarithmetical]], and the first [[admissible ordinal]] after ''ω''.

